  "headline20": "Critical operational constraints are flagged at 13 airports right now.",
  "management45": "Critical operational constraints are flagged at 13 airports right now. No engine anti-ice operations are currently flagged. Across base airports: 1 critical, 7 high, 13 medium, 18 normal. Key bases needing attention include Rome–Fiumicino Leonardo da Vinci (FCO/LIRF), Larnaca (LCA/LCLK) and M. R. Štefánik (BTS/LZIB); plus 5 other bases. 13 additional base airports are at medium severity and should be monitored closely. At base airports, the dominant pattern is thunderstorm / convective risk  — most notably around David the Builder Kutaisi (KUT/UGKO), Rome–Fiumicino Leonardo da Vinci (FCO/LIRF) and Larnaca (LCA/LCLK). Network hotspots: Ben Gurion (TLV/LLBG), Tenerife Sur (TFS/GCTS), Al Massira (AGA/GMAD), Brussels South Charleroi (CRL/EBCI), Frankfurt-Hahn (HHN/EDFH) and 8 others. Primary drivers: low cloud base, snow / blowing snow and thunderstorm / convective risk. Expected impact is reduced runway capacity with higher delay and diversion risk, especially where visibility/RVR and cloud base are very low. Since the last update, 8 airports changed status, led by Ben Gurion (TLV/LLBG), Sphinx (SPX/HESX), Turku (TKU/EFTU) and 5 others.",
  "detail90": "Critical operational constraints are flagged at 13 airports right now. Base airports (focus): Rome–Fiumicino Leonardo da Vinci (FCO/LIRF) — HIGH: strong gusts risk | Larnaca (LCA/LCLK) — HIGH: strong gusts risk | M. R. Štefánik (BTS/LZIB) — HIGH: strong gusts risk | Venice Marco Polo (VCE/LIPZ) — HIGH: thunderstorm / convective risk | Vienna (VIE/LOWW) — HIGH: strong gusts risk | Zvartnots (EVN/UDYZ) — HIGH: thunderstorm / convective risk and 2 others. Worst affected now: Ben Gurion (TLV/LLBG) — CRIT: strong gusts risk; visibility down to 1 km (drivers: thunderstorm/convective risk) | Tenerife Sur (TFS/GCTS) — CRIT: strong gusts risk; cloud base around 0 ft (drivers: operational constraints) | Al Massira (AGA/GMAD) — CRIT: mist; visibility down to 2 km, cloud base around 100 ft; below approach minima (current METAR) (drivers: approach minima limits, low ceilings, mist) | Brussels South Charleroi (CRL/EBCI) — CRIT: snow; visibility down to 1.5 km, cloud base around 300 ft (drivers: low ceilings, thunderstorm/convective risk, snow/blowing snow) | Frankfurt-Hahn (HHN/EDFH) — CRIT: snow; visibility down to 2.5 km, cloud base around 400 ft (drivers: low ceilings, thunderstorm/convective risk, snow/blowing snow) | Memmingen Allgau (FMM/EDJA) — CRIT: snow; visibility down to 1.2 km, cloud base around 400 ft (drivers: low ceilings, snow/blowing snow) and 7 others. Changed since last run: Ben Gurion (TLV/LLBG), Sphinx (SPX/HESX), Turku (TKU/EFTU), Hurghada (HRG/HEGN), Marsa Alam (RMF/HEMA), Seve Ballesteros-Santander (SDR/LEXJ), Priština Adem Jashari (PRN/BKPR), Sharm El Sheikh (SSH/HESH).",
